{{Infobox country at games | NOC = KAZ | NOCname = [[National Olympic Committee of the Republic of Kazakhstan]] | oldcode = | year = 1994 | date = | games = Asian Games | location = [[Hiroshima]] | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | officials = | gold = 27 | silver = 25 | bronze = 27 | rank = 4 | appearances = auto | seealso = | website = }}
The '''1994 [[Asian Games]]''' also known as '''XII Asiad''' were held from October 2 to October 16, 1994 in [[Hiroshima]], [[Japan]]. The main theme of this edition was to promote peace and harmony among Asian nations. It was emphasized by the host because the venue was the site of the first [[Atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki|atomic bomb attack]] 49 years earlier. Due to the [[First Gulf War]], Iraq was suspended from the games.<ref name="beijing ">{{cite web|url=http://en.beijing2008.cn/58/81/article212058158.shtml |title=Past Asian Games &ndash; Hiroshima 1994 Asian Games |publisher=beijing2008.cn (official website of 2008 Beijing Olympics) |date=November 22, 2006 |accessdate=May 26, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130617120725/http://en.beijing2008.cn/58/81/article212058158.shtml |archivedate=June 17, 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref name="gz2010">{{cite web | url=http://www.gz2010.cn/08/0427/17/4AI8DV6I0078003F.html | title=12th Asian Games Hiroshima 1994 - Poppo & CuCCu | publisher=gz2010.cn (official website of 2010 Asian Games) | work=GAGOC | date=April 27, 2008 | accessdate=May 26, 2011}}</ref>
