{{Infobox gymnast | name = Sara Radman | gender = w | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = | altname = | nickname = | country = {{flagu|Germany}} | regions = | formercountry = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|7|20|df=y}} | birth_place = | hometown = | residence = | death_date = | death_place = | height = | discipline = RG | level = Senior International Elite | natlteam = 2009–2013 (?) | club = | gym = | collegeteam = | headcoach = | assistcoach = | formercoach = | choreographer = | music = | eponymousskills = | retired = | worldranking = | updated = | show-medals = yes | medaltemplates = <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> }}
'''Sara Radman''' (born 20 July 1993) is a German group [[rhythmic gymnast]]. She represents her nation at international competitions.
She participated at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in London.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/olympics/2012/athletes/7ffc775d-48be-41b4-bdb6-bed632830a7f |title=BBC Sport - London 2012 Olympics - Sara Radman : Germany, Gymnastics - Rhythmic |website=Bbc.co.uk |date=2012-08-13 |accessdate=2017-03-07}}</ref> She also competed at world championships, including at the 2009, 2010, 2011 and [[2013 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2011 World Rhythmic Gymnastics Championships athletes – Sara Radman |url=http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/00000A010100FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF02 |publisher=Longinestiming.com |date= |accessdate=27 January 2016}}</ref>
