{{unreferenced|date=August 2011}} {{Infobox venue| | stadium_name = Institute of Physical Education Sukhothai Stadium | former_names = Bunsom Martin Stadium | image = [[File:Sukhothai Stadium.jpg|200px]] | location = [[Sukhothai Province|Sukhothai]], [[Thailand]] | coordinates = {{coord|16.975134|99.789532|format=dms|type:landmark_scale:3000}} | opened = 2009 | owner = Institute of Physical Education, Sukhothai | operator = Institute of Physical Education, Sukhothai | surface = Grass | construction_cost = | nickname = Sukhothai Stadium | tenants = | seating_capacity = 4,500 }} The '''Sukhothai Institute of Physical Education Stadium''' or '''Sukhothai Province Stadium''' ({{lang-th|สนามกีฬา สพล. สุโขทัย หรือ สนามกีฬาจังหวัดสุโขทัย หรือ สนามกีฬาบุญสม มาติน}}) is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Sukhothai Province]], [[Thailand]], built to host the [[Sukhothai F.C.]] in [[Thailand Division 2 League]] from 2009 to 2013. The stadium is made up of a main stand with a capacity of 2,500 and second stand on the opposite side of the field with a capacity of 2,000. Only the main stand has seats and is covered, the second stand is uncovered and is made of concrete steps. The stadium is also fitted with an electronic scoreboard and is also used by the local public for various events.
==Main stand== The main stand has a maximum capacity of 2,500 (All seated) and also contains most facilities including changing rooms, meeting rooms and a media room.
